National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with Chinese human rights advocates to discuss concerns about human rights and religious freedom in China. The participants discussed issues such as the removal of crosses from churches, demolition of houses of worship, restrictions on Ramadan and other Muslim practices, crackdown on human rights lawyers, and the importance of preserving space for civil society. Rice reiterated the US commitment to promoting human rights globally and supporting the protection of human rights, including religious freedom, in China. She also emphasized that improving human rights conditions is in China's long-term interest and will continue to be a topic of discussion in US-China dialogue.